pacman -Qi - Give information about installed packages
pacsearch <package> - Search for packages
pacman -Ql <package> - List all the files associated with the installed package
pacman -Qlq <package> - Will also lists the files associated with a package but without the package name.
pacman -Qql <package> | grep bin ⇒ this will display executables in bin folder
sudo pacman -Sw <package> - Download the package without installing it
sudo pacman -U <package_path> - Install a package from path or URL
pacman -Qu ⇒ Display all the packages that need to be updated
sudo pacman -Qen ⇒ Display after installed packages
 
ls /var/cache/pacman/pkg | grep linux ⇒ Lists downloaded packages
pacman -U <path_to_cached_file> ⇒ Downgrade to a specific downloaded package
